        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 2:18AM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 217 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Regan, or 19 miles northeast of Bismarck, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wing, Regan, Baldwin, New Johns Lake, and Arena.
</description>
        <instruction>A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
south central North Dakota.</instruction>
